918
00:53:47.612 --> 00:53:51.552
So, in addition to the most common urothelial carcinoma,

919
00:53:51.652 --> 00:53:55.072
which we will call UCNOS for short, there are around

920
00:53:55.492 --> 00:53:59.172
20 to 30% of bladder tumors can, out of

921
00:53:59.492 --> 00:54:03.082
varying histologies, showing, for example, squamous,

922
00:54:03.412 --> 00:54:07.362
glandular, or small cell neuroendocrine cell-like morphology.

923
00:54:07.952 --> 00:54:11.752
In these histologic classifications is clinically important

924
00:54:11.912 --> 00:54:15.172
as they correlate with distinct prognosis.

925
00:54:15.502 --> 00:54:19.352
And as shown here, the UCNOS group is of a

926
00:54:20.272 --> 00:54:24.072
relatively better prognosis, while subtypes such

927
00:54:24.172 --> 00:54:28.072
as sarcomatoid, squamous, and plasmacytoid

928
00:54:28.332 --> 00:54:31.612
are usually associated with a worse clinical outcome.

929
00:54:32.172 --> 00:54:35.672
So in order to understand the underlying

930
00:54:35.712 --> 00:54:39.392
biology of this phenotypic plasticity, our team has

931
00:54:39.452 --> 00:54:43.132
