for this opportunity

1583
01:32:17.456 --> 01:32:20.645
to discuss our program on peroxiredoxin 3 and

1584
01:32:20.676 --> 01:32:21.566
mesothelioma,

1585
01:32:22.416 --> 01:32:23.316
as well as our

1586
01:32:24.236 --> 01:32:26.536
efforts to target this clinically in mesothelioma.

1587
01:32:29.396 --> 01:32:33.276
So pleural mesothelioma is a tumor that arises from

1588
01:32:33.336 --> 01:32:37.006
the occupational exposure to asbestos and primarily

1589
01:32:37.136 --> 01:32:40.866
targets the lining of the pleural cavity, the mesothelial cell lining of

1590
01:32:40.916 --> 01:32:43.976
the cavity. It's a

1591
01:32:44.076 --> 01:32:48.036
slow-growing, long-latency tumor that takes about 20 to 40

1592
01:32:48.056 --> 01:32:51.096
years to develop after a possible exposure.

1593
01:32:52.076 --> 01:32:53.936
It has limited therapeutic options.

1594
01:32:54.516 --> 01:32:57.896
Just a few years ago, an immunotherapy doublet was approved for the treatment of

1595
01:32:57.916 --> 01:32:58.696
mesothelioma,

1596
01:32:59.776 --> 01:33:03.336
and it had some success, but nothing groundbreaking.

1597
01:33:04.126 --> 01:33:07.566
And the five-year survival rate is pretty low, 10% to 15%.

1598
01:33:07.566 --> 01:33:11.216
And so after this 20- to 40-year latency period, the aggressiveness of the tumor

1599
01:33:12.936 --> 01:33:14.356
leaves little options for patients.

1600
01:33:15.916 --> 01:33:19.866
Mesothelioma can be characterized as a redox-driven tumor, as a number of other

1601
01:33:19.876 --> 01:33:23.666
solid tumors can as well. And the characterization is that

1602
01:33:23.676 --> 01:33:27.656
reactive oxygen species, which are important for all cells, normal

1603
01:33:27.756 --> 01:33:31.356
and in disease states, can drive signaling pathways that

1604
01:33:31.396 --> 01:33:35.216
support the tumorigenic state. So tumor cells try to

1605
01:33:35.256 --> 01:33:38.916
survive in this sort of Goldilocks state, where under high levels of reactive

1606
01:33:38.976 --> 01:33:42.776
oxygen species, they overexpress antioxidant enzyme

1607
01:33:42.876 --> 01:33:46.856
pathways to protect them from the cytotoxic properties of reactive oxygen species.

1608
01:33:47.546 --> 01:33:51.526
So mesothelioma cells have increased levels of mitochondrial reactive oxygen

1609
01:33:51.596 --> 01:33:55.526
species primarily. We've shown that the key antioxidant enzymes

1610
01:33:55.556 --> 01:33:59.496
in the mitochondria are overexpressed in mesothelioma cells and tumor tissue.

1611
01:34:00.236 --> 01:34:03.736
And not only is the protein levels of these antioxidants increased, but the

1612
01:34:03.816 --> 01:34:07.645
activity of these antioxidants is also increased, really highlighting

1613
01:34:07.645 --> 01:34:10.896
the importance of balancing redox status in mesothelioma

1614
01:34:10.916 --> 01:34:12.436
tumors for their survival.

1615
01:34:15.316 --> 01:34:18.736
We focused on an enzyme called peroxiredoxin 3, which is

1616
01:34:18.776 --> 01:34:21.176
exclusively expressed in the mitochondrial matrix.

1617
01:34:21.396 --> 01:34:25.336
And peroxiredoxin 3 has a very interesting biochemical

1618
01:34:25.736 --> 01:34:29.356
reaction where in the presence of hydrogen

1619
01:34:29.396 --> 01:34:32.976
peroxide in the mitochondrial matrix, two critical cysteine

1620
01:34:33.016 --> 01:34:36.966
residues are involved in a redox reaction leading to a

1621
01:34:37.076 --> 01:34:40.496
disulfide bond that can be

1622
01:34:40.556 --> 01:34:43.076
regenerated by the thioredoxin system in the mitochondria.

1623
01:34:43.556 --> 01:34:47.456
So this enzyme's constantly cycling in the matrix to protect cells from peroxide,

1624
01:34:47.916 --> 01:34:50.896
and it's the most active and abundant antioxidant in the mitochondria.

1625
01:34:52.716 --> 01:34:56.656
Importantly, PRRX3 has been shown to protect tumor cells from oxidative stress,

1626
01:34:57.176 --> 01:35:01.126
and data from the Broad Institute and the PRISM screening has shown that deletion

1627
01:35:01.136 --> 01:35:04.826
of PRRX3 is lethal in most tumor cells, as shown in this schematic

1628
01:35:04.896 --> 01:35:08.686
here. Importantly, though, you can genetically delete PRRX3 from all tissues,

1629
01:35:09.076 --> 01:35:12.826
and these animals have no significant phenotype, highlighting its possibility as

1630
01:35:13.036 --> 01:35:16.016
a unique and actionable therapeutic target in oncology.

1631
01:35:18.216 --> 01:35:21.316
To characterize the importance of PRRX3 in mesothelioma, we generated

1632
01:35:21.336 --> 01:35:24.696
CRISPR-deleted human mesothelioma tumor cell lines

1633
01:35:25.316 --> 01:35:29.116
of biphasic histology. Here we've shown that we can effectively

1634
01:35:29.136 --> 01:35:31.076
delete the PRRX3 enzyme, and

1635
01:35:31.996 --> 01:35:35.536
the byproducts of this is a significant reduction in cell proliferation

1636
01:35:35.956 --> 01:35:39.656
as well as the ability of these tumor cells to form colonies in a

1637
01:35:39.716 --> 01:35:40.796
colony formation assay.

1638
01:35:42.026 --> 01:35:45.996
Additionally, their ability to grow in Matrigel is significantly disrupted.

1639
01:35:46.246 --> 01:35:49.676
And when we take these tumors and we inject them into the peritoneal cavity of SCID

1640
01:35:49.716 --> 01:35:53.296
mice, they fail to form tumors, as shown in this graph in the

1641
01:35:53.335 --> 01:35:57.316
histology of the tissue taken from the animals, really underlying the importance

1642
01:35:57.376 --> 01:36:00.476
of PRRX3 in mesothelioma tumor cell growth.

1643
01:36:02.816 --> 01:36:06.656
In addition, we did some functional characteristics of these cells when we

1644
01:36:06.696 --> 01:36:10.636
deleted PRRX3, it being the most primary and important antioxidant in the

1645
01:36:10.656 --> 01:36:14.356
mitochondria. We measured levels of hydrogen peroxide in the

1646
01:36:14.376 --> 01:36:18.276
mitochondrial matrix using a genetically encoded hydrogen peroxide sensor

1647
01:36:18.316 --> 01:36:21.836
called Hyper7. And as you can see both in the images and the

1648
01:36:21.876 --> 01:36:25.826
quantification, the deletion of PRRX3 significantly increases the

1649
01:36:25.876 --> 01:36:28.636
levels of hydrogen peroxide in the mitochondria of these cells.

1650
01:36:29.996 --> 01:36:30.696
In addition,

1651
01:36:31.976 --> 01:36:35.876
looking at readouts of both mitochondrial bioenergetics, looking at oxygen

1652
01:36:35.896 --> 01:36:39.296
consumption rates, we see a significant reduction in

1653
01:36:40.236 --> 01:36:43.656
all aspects of mitochondrial bioenergetics when we delete PRRX3,

1654
01:36:44.256 --> 01:36:48.176
as well as the reduction in extracellular acidification rate, which can be

1655
01:36:48.236 --> 01:36:50.156
an indirect readout of glycolysis.

1656
01:36:50.816 --> 01:36:54.666
So deletion of PRRX3 causes what seems to be a global metabolic defect in these

1657
01:36:54.676 --> 01:36:55.276
tumor cells.

1658
01:36:57.516 --> 01:37:01.396
To confirm this, we generated cell lines where we re-expressed a FLAG-tag

1659
01:37:01.456 --> 01:37:05.436
version of the protein back into the knockout cell line, as

1660
01:37:05.446 --> 01:37:09.176
shown here. This significantly rescued

1661
01:37:09.216 --> 01:37:13.176
hydrogen peroxide levels in the mitochondrial matrix of the PRRX3

1662
01:37:13.556 --> 01:37:16.996
knockdown cells by reducing Hyper7 expression, completely

1663
01:37:17.056 --> 01:37:20.556
restored mitochondrial bioenergetics, and completely restored

1664
01:37:20.636 --> 01:37:24.576
extracellular acidification rates, highlighting the critical role of PRRX3

1665
01:37:24.636 --> 01:37:25.936
in cellular metabolism.

1666
01:37:27.196 --> 01:37:30.916
In addition, the re-expression of PRRX3 back into these cell

1667
01:37:31.016 --> 01:37:34.596
lines led to a partial rescue of colony formation in a colony

1668
01:37:34.616 --> 01:37:35.036
formation

1669
01:37:35.096 --> 01:37:39.088
assay.We've conducted

1670
01:37:39.188 --> 01:37:42.888
RNA sequencing on these cells, comparing our wild-type cell lines to our

1671
01:37:42.928 --> 01:37:46.898
PRRX3 knockout cells. You can see PRRX3 being one of the number one knocked down

1672
01:37:46.948 --> 01:37:50.528
or reduced expressed genes. And a number of the pathways

1673
01:37:50.788 --> 01:37:54.658
seem to be very important in both metabolism and reactive oxygen species,

1674
01:37:55.048 --> 01:37:57.148
as well as cell proliferation and growth.

1675
01:37:59.008 --> 01:38:02.308
In addition, when we rescue PRRX3 expression through the expression of the

1676
01:38:02.348 --> 01:38:05.978
endogenous flag-tagged protein, we see a number of very interesting pathways,

1677
01:38:06.008 --> 01:38:09.688
including oxidative phosphorylation and glycolysis and hypoxia being

1678
01:38:09.748 --> 01:38:11.968
rescued upon the reintroduction of PRRX3.

1679
01:38:12.508 --> 01:38:16.418
So this is very early in hypothesis-generating data that is allowing us to look at

1680
01:38:16.428 --> 01:38:20.328
the role of this mitochondrial matrix enzyme in control of a number

1681
01:38:20.388 --> 01:38:22.488
of different gene expression patterns.

1682
01:38:24.928 --> 01:38:28.648
So years ago, we first identified a mechanism of

1683
01:38:28.688 --> 01:38:32.468
action of this large and quite ugly-looking compound, thiostrepton,

1684
01:38:32.948 --> 01:38:36.868
as being a covalent inhibitor of the peroxiredoxin III enzyme.

1685
01:38:36.928 --> 01:38:40.808
And what we've discovered is that in the catalytic cycle of

1686
01:38:40.828 --> 01:38:44.348
peroxiredoxin III, upon disulfide formation at one

1687
01:38:44.388 --> 01:38:48.058
catalytic active site, this now exposes a secondary active

1688
01:38:48.168 --> 01:38:51.828
site that allows for thiostrepton to form a covalent linkage

1689
01:38:51.928 --> 01:38:55.308
across two critical active site cysteine residues.

1690
01:38:55.348 --> 01:38:57.248
This is an irreversible modification.

1691
01:38:57.588 --> 01:38:59.588
It can be detected on a protein western blot,

1692
01:39:00.788 --> 01:39:04.288
as a shift in molecular weight that cannot be reduced with conventional

1693
01:39:04.708 --> 01:39:07.008
or pretty much any reducing agent thrown at it.

1694
01:39:07.948 --> 01:39:11.898
We've shown that this induces significant oxidative stress in tumor cells, leading

1695
01:39:11.928 --> 01:39:15.788
to tumor cell death. And we've shown that the cysteine residues, both the

1696
01:39:16.828 --> 01:39:20.368
resolving and peroxidatic cysteine of peroxiredoxin III to be

1697
01:39:20.408 --> 01:39:23.328
critical for this dimerization to occur.

1698
01:39:23.348 --> 01:39:26.958
Whereas if we mutate a non-catalytic cysteine to a serine in PRRX3, we still get

1699
01:39:27.008 --> 01:39:30.398
the cross-linking. So we've characterized the active site cross-linking and

1700
01:39:30.468 --> 01:39:31.748
mechanism of this compound.

1701
01:39:33.608 --> 01:39:37.448
Thiostrepton has also been investigated by the Broad Institute in the PRISM screen

1702
01:39:37.468 --> 01:39:41.238
and shown to have quite abundant activity in a number of

1703
01:39:41.268 --> 01:39:43.628
different tumor cell lines, as shown here on the

1704
01:39:43.688 --> 01:39:47.307
left. We've shown activity in mesothelioma cell

1705
01:39:47.348 --> 01:39:47.888
models,

1706
01:39:48.807 --> 01:39:52.148
and a therapeutic window between normal and tumor cells.

1707
01:39:52.708 --> 01:39:55.188
And we've also shown in a number of mouse models, both

1708
01:39:55.588 --> 01:39:59.318
immunosuppressed and immunocompetent mouse models, the ability

1709
01:39:59.728 --> 01:40:02.008
for thiostrepton to induce anti-tumor activity.

1710
01:40:03.928 --> 01:40:07.918
This data and significant other data not presented today supported the clinical

1711
01:40:07.988 --> 01:40:11.028
development of thiostrepton as RS-021,

1712
01:40:12.308 --> 01:40:16.048
which is the clinical formulation of three mg per ml solution, and the start of the

1713
01:40:16.088 --> 01:40:20.048
MITOPE clinical trial, which is focused on patients who have malignant

1714
01:40:20.108 --> 01:40:23.828
pleural effusions rising from mesothelioma or metastatic disease.

1715
01:40:24.648 --> 01:40:28.548
These patients are given an intrapleural catheter to drain the

1716
01:40:28.568 --> 01:40:32.528
pleural effusion liquid, and then RS-021 is a local regional therapy that is

1717
01:40:33.268 --> 01:40:35.328
injected directly back into the pleural cavity.

1718
01:40:36.368 --> 01:40:39.968
And these patients can secure their IPC, and this is a

1719
01:40:40.088 --> 01:40:42.688
once-a-week treatment until disease progression.

1720
01:40:43.388 --> 01:40:45.948
Here's some data from the Phase 1 clinical trial where we showed

1721
01:40:46.428 --> 01:40:50.288
plasma levels of thiostrepton when injected intrapleurally are

1722
01:40:50.368 --> 01:40:53.948
actually relatively low, so the treatment is being contained to the pleural

1723
01:40:53.988 --> 01:40:54.768
cavity.

1724
01:40:55.588 --> 01:40:59.288
We are able to see that the protein cross-linking of the PRRX3

1725
01:40:59.328 --> 01:41:02.928
enzyme is occurring in pleural effusions derived from these patients, so the

1726
01:41:02.948 --> 01:41:04.937
mechanism of action is retained in these patients.

1727
01:41:05.358 --> 01:41:07.958
We had a number of drainages on the course of treatment.

1728
01:41:09.448 --> 01:41:13.348
Here's data from the Phase 1 showing individual patient responses, so

1729
01:41:13.388 --> 01:41:17.368
a spider plot showing radiological activity of the drug against

1730
01:41:17.388 --> 01:41:20.708
the tumors, with some patients having significant and persistent

1731
01:41:20.768 --> 01:41:21.428
responses.

1732
01:41:22.968 --> 01:41:26.898
Our progression-free survival was in line with a majority of treatments already

1733
01:41:26.948 --> 01:41:30.558
available to patients, and our overall survival is showing

1734
01:41:30.568 --> 01:41:32.398
meaningful impact for these patients.

1735
01:41:33.748 --> 01:41:37.657
So the MITOPE Phase 1 trial met its primary endpoint of safety and tolerability,

1736
01:41:37.708 --> 01:41:40.958
and our Phase 2 testing has recently completed in the past months.

1737
01:41:42.128 --> 01:41:43.798
This data will be presented later this year.

1738
01:41:45.088 --> 01:41:48.548
In an effort to understand biomarkers that could predict

1739
01:41:48.948 --> 01:41:52.878
response and treatment effects, we conducted explant testing

1740
01:41:52.908 --> 01:41:56.627
of taking surgically removed patient tumors and testing them ex

1741
01:41:56.668 --> 01:41:59.548
vivo for activity against the thiostrepton drug.

1742
01:42:00.088 --> 01:42:03.808
And using markers such as cytokeratin, cleaved PARP, and Ki-67,

1743
01:42:04.228 --> 01:42:08.088
we can now look at the response of these tumor tissues ex vivo and characterize

1744
01:42:08.128 --> 01:42:08.748
responses.

1745
01:42:09.708 --> 01:42:12.968
So in this waterfall plot, these are all individual patient-derived explants that

1746
01:42:13.008 --> 01:42:16.178
are either responding or not responding to the treatment.

1747
01:42:16.638 --> 01:42:20.508
And with this, we can conduct RNA sequencing and not showing all the data.

1748
01:42:20.548 --> 01:42:24.318
One of the top hits that came out of our screen was the increased

1749
01:42:24.388 --> 01:42:27.998
expression of SLC7A11 in non-responding patient explants.

1750
01:42:29.688 --> 01:42:33.608
SLC7A11 is a protein in the plasma membrane

1751
01:42:33.668 --> 01:42:33.998
that

1752
01:42:35.048 --> 01:42:38.218
supports the export of glutamate and import of

1753
01:42:38.228 --> 01:42:41.998
cysteine, primarily used for glutathione synthesis and protection of

1754
01:42:42.008 --> 01:42:45.808
cells from oxidative stress and lipid-induced cell death through

1755
01:42:45.828 --> 01:42:46.548
ferroptosis.

1756
01:42:48.308 --> 01:42:52.128
We confirm the importance of SLC7A11 in thiostrepton

1757
01:42:52.188 --> 01:42:56.168
treatment by using siRNA to SLC7A11, and

1758
01:42:56.208 --> 01:42:59.828
you can see a significant reduction in IC50

1759
01:43:00.188 --> 01:43:03.188
